etcd version 3
-----------------------
etcdctl snapshot save 
etcdctl endpoint health
etcdctl get
etcdctl put


kubectl
-------
1. kubectl config set-context $(kubectl config current-context) --namespace=dev


Taint commands
--------------
1. kubectl taint nodes node-name key=value:taint-effect
   here taint-effect can be three types
        - NoSchedule - No new pod will be schedule on this node
        - PreferNoSchedule - system will not schedule pod on this node but do not gurantee
        - NoExecute  - No new pod will be schedule on this node and existing will be evicted if they are not taint tolerant


- kubectl label node <node-name> <key>=<value> -> To label a node

- kubectl get events -o wide -> for checking which schedular is picked.

- kubectl exec kube-apiserver-controlplane -n kube-system -- kube-apiserver -
h | grep enable-admission-plugins -> To see all enable-admission-plugins

- kubectl -n webhook-demo create secret tls webhook-server-tls \
    --cert "/root/keys/webhook-server-tls.crt" \
    --key "/root/keys/webhook-server-tls.key"

- kubectl rollout status <deployment name>
- kubectl rollout history <deployment name>
- kubectl rollout undo <deployment name>